# =============================================================================
# FASHIONHUB ECOMMERCE - ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES TEMPLATE
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env.local to version control

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED)
# =============================================================================

# Your Supabase project URL
# Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > General > Reference ID
# Format: https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# Your Supabase anonymous key (public key)
# Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project API keys > anon public
# Safe to use in client-side code
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Your Supabase service role key (private key)
# Found in: Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API > Project API keys > service_role
# ⚠️  KEEP THIS SECRET - Only use server-side, never expose to client
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Create a Supabase account at https://supabase.com
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Wait for project initialization (2-3 minutes)
# 4. Navigate to Settings > General to find your project URL
# 5. Navigate to Settings > API to find your keys
# 6. Copy the values above and paste them in .env.local
# 7. Set up Google OAuth in Supabase Dashboard:
#    - Go to Authentication > Settings
#    - Enable Google provider
#    - Configure Google OAuth credentials from Google Cloud Console
# 8. Run database setup:
#    - Execute SQL schema in Supabase SQL Editor (see supabase.sql)
#    - Set up Row Level Security policies
# 9. (Optional) Seed sample data:
#    npm run upload-images && npm run seed-tshirts

# =============================================================================
# GOOGLE OAUTH SETUP (REQUIRED FOR AUTHENTICATION)
# =============================================================================

# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com)
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Enable Google+ API
# 4. Go to Credentials > Create Credentials > OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# 5. Set application type to "Web application"
# 6. Add authorized redirect URIs:
#    - https://YOUR_SUPABASE_URL/auth/v1/callback
#    - Replace YOUR_SUPABASE_URL with your actual Supabase project URL
# 7. Copy Client ID and Client Secret to Supabase Dashboard:
#    - Authentication > Settings > Auth Providers > Google
#    - Enable Google provider and paste your credentials

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# For production deployment, set these same variables in your hosting platform:

# Vercel:
# - Go to Project Settings > Environment Variables
# - Add each variable with production values

# Netlify:
# - Go to Site Settings > Environment Variables  
# - Add each variable with production values

# Railway/DigitalOcean:
# - Set environment variables in your deployment configuration

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================

# ✅ DO:
# - Use .env.local for local development (automatically ignored by git)
# - Use different Supabase projects for development and production
# - Enable Row Level Security (RLS) on all tables in production
# - Keep service role key secret and use only server-side

# ❌ DON'T:
# - Commit .env.local or any file containing actual secrets
# - Use service role key in client-side code
# - Share your service role key in code, screenshots, or documentation
# - Use the same Supabase project for development and production

# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================

# Common issues and solutions:

# 1. "Invalid API key" or "Invalid JWT"
#    - Check that URLs and keys match your Supabase project exactly
#    - Ensure no extra spaces or characters in environment variables
#    - Verify your Supabase project is active and not paused

# 2. "Authentication failed" or OAuth not working
#    - Verify Google OAuth setup in Google Cloud Console
#    - Check redirect URIs match exactly (including https/http)
#    - Ensure Google provider is enabled in Supabase Auth settings

# 3. "Database connection failed" or permission errors
#    - Ensure Supabase project is active and accessible
#    - Check Row Level Security policies are properly configured
#    - Verify SQL schema has been executed in Supabase

# 4. App not loading or build errors
#    - Ensure all three environment variables are set
#    - Restart development server after changing .env.local
#    - Clear Next.js cache: rm -rf .next && npm run dev

# Need help?
# - Supabase documentation: https://supabase.com/docs
# - Next.js environment variables: https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/environment-variables
# - Project README: ./README.md

